# Implementation Plan - InsightPilot: Executive Decision Intelligence Platform

InsightPilot (originally referred to as BoardRoom AI) is a production-grade Executive Decision Intelligence Platform that digests heterogeneous business data (revenue logs, customer metrics, usage logs, feedback logs) and transforms it into actionable executive recommendations, KPI explanations, anomaly alerts, and structured business reviews using Streamlit, Plotly, SQLite, and the Gemini API.

## Proposed System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Data Sources
        CSV[Uploaded/Mock CSV Files] --> |Ingest| DataGen[Data Generator & Loader]
        DB[(SQLite Database)] --> |Query/Store| DBStore[Database Manager]
    end

    subgraph Data Processing & Analytics
        DataGen --> AnalEngine[Analytics Engine]
        DBStore --> AnalEngine
        AnalEngine --> |KPI Tracking| KPIs[KPI Engine]
        AnalEngine --> |Segmentation & Trends| Retention[Retention & Cohorts]
    end

    subgraph AI Engine
        KPIs --> AIEngine[AI Strategy Engine]
        Retention --> AIEngine
        AIEngine --> |Prompt Engineering| Gemini[Gemini API / LLM]
        Gemini --> |Insights, Risks, Actions| Reports[Executive Reporter]
    end

    subgraph Presentation Layer
        KPIs --> Dashboard[Streamlit App]
        Retention --> Dashboard
        Reports --> Dashboard
        Dashboard --> |User Uploads & Chat Queries| AnalEngine
    end
```

## Database Schema (SQLite)

We will use SQLite for a lightweight, production-grade self-contained local relational database. It will house historical KPI logs, uploaded data audit logs, and generated executive reports.

```sql
-- Historical Executive Reports
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS executive_reports (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    report_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'weekly', 'monthly', 'board'
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    content TEXT NOT NULL,      -- Markdown generated by AI
    metrics_summary TEXT        -- JSON snapshot of KPIs at time of generation
);

-- User Query Logs (for audit and alignment analysis)
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS strategy_queries (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    query_text TEXT NOT NULL,
    response_text TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- Business Metrics Audit (Logs uploaded dataset metadata)
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS data_uploads (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    filename TEXT NOT NULL,
    row_count INTEGER NOT NULL,
    uploaded_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    data_type TEXT NOT NULL     -- 'revenue', 'customer', 'feedback', 'product'
);
```

